                  <!-- ********* <decoDesc> ********* -->
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote ana="#xx">
                        <ab>Inscription is set in four lines in the middle panel of the fourth band, featuring 
                    the showbread table.  The upper portion of the panel with most of the Greek inscription
                    was cut out in antiquity and replaced with an Aramaic inscription. Only the last letter of
                    each line, as well as the leg of the xi before the alpha in the third line, remain.  The
                    original length of the lines can be reconstructed on the basis of line 4, containing 16
                    letters - about the same length as line 2 of inscription 14 which contains 15 letters. The
                    four lines probably filled the entire breadth of the central panel.  If so, either line 3
                    was somewhat short or, more likely, the last E in line 2 did not belong to the verb ἐποίησεν
                    but was part of the donor's patrynomic.</ab>
                        <locus/>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
